wiki.summary: “infinity (888)” is the second collaboration between X and Joey, following “King’s Dead (Freestyle).” They planned to collaborate on a full project, but X tragically passed in June 2018, shelving plans of a joint album. XXXTENTACION also has a track off of Members Only, Vol. 3 called “777”, which features fellow Florida artist and friend, KiD TRUNKS. This can be seen as a sequel to that. “777” means to release your fears, “888” means positive and progressive changes. Read more on Last.fm.
wiki.content: “infinity (888)” is the second collaboration between X and Joey, following “King’s Dead (Freestyle).” They planned to collaborate on a full project, but X tragically passed in June 2018, shelving plans of a joint album. XXXTENTACION also has a track off of Members Only, Vol. 3 called “777”, which features fellow Florida artist and friend, KiD TRUNKS. This can be seen as a sequel to that. “777” means to release your fears, “888” means positive and progressive changes. X, in the last few months of his life, was trying to promote positivity and change. This song samples “The Peacocks” by Stan Getz and Bill Evans, as well as heavily sampling the instrumental from “Life” by Proof. Read more on Last.fm.
